/* unit_reached.pk - Cover the reachability record: h5policy_mark_reached and
   the report-time lookups over it.

   The visited sets exist to break cycles, so they hold only the kinds that need
   deduplicating; a consumer asking "did the walk reach these bytes?" about a
   heap or an array block gets a false negative from them.  The reachability
   record answers that question instead.

   The load-bearing property here is that recording is walk-budget neutral.
   h5policy_seen_u64 charges its scan to the operation budget, so a deduplicated
   record would add an O(N^2) term to it and could push a large file past
   max_walk_operations -- a reporting feature silently changing a verdict.
   h5policy_mark_reached must therefore never tick, and these cases pin that.

   Prints one "PASS <name>" / "FAIL <name>" line per case and exits 0 only if
   every case passed.  */

/* Copyright (C) 2026 The HDF Group.  */

/* This program is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify
